
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `apport-collect` baraye jam'avari etela'at dar morede crash-ha va moshkelat barname-ha estefade mishavad. In etela'at be developer-ha komak mikonad ta moshkelat ra peyda va hal konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `apport-collect -p <esm-e-package>`  --> 📦 Jam'avari etela'at baraye yek package khass. Esme package bayad dorost vared shavad.
    🔹 `apport-collect <PID>` --> 🆔 Jam'avari etela'at baraye yek process ba PID moshakhas. PID ra az dastoor `ps` ya `top` mitavan gereft.
    🔹 `apport-collect` --> 🐞 Dar soorate run shodan bad az crash, etela'at crash ra jam'avari mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ apport-collect -p firefox

    🔹 Jam'avari etela'at baraye package "firefox".

    $ apport-collect 1234

    🔹 Jam'avari etela'at baraye processi ke PID-ash 1234 ast.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ apport-collect

    🔹 Agar be tore mostaghim bad az crash barname run shavad, etela'ate crash ra jam'avari mikonad va baraye developers mifrestad ta moshkel ra hal konand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `apport-collect` command is used to collect information about crashes and program problems.  This information helps developers find and fix the issues.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `apport-collect -p <package-name>` --> 📦 Collect information for a specific package. The package name must be entered correctly.
    🔹 `apport-collect <PID>` --> 🆔 Collect information for a process with a specific PID. The PID can be obtained from the `ps` or `top` commands.
    🔹 `apport-collect` --> 🐞 If run directly after a crash, it collects crash information.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ apport-collect -p firefox

    🔹 Collect information for the "firefox" package.

    $ apport-collect 1234

    🔹 Collect information for the process whose PID is 1234.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ apport-collect

    🔹 If run directly after a program crash, it collects the crash information and sends it to developers to help resolve the issue.
